  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight: it characterises discovered failures by reporting where and how they occur (counts of errors per environmental type, comparisons across conditions) and by using neuron-level coverage metrics (KMNC and NBC) and coverage increases as part of the fitness/search objective. However, it does not trace failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., dataset bias, spurious features, corrupted training data, or overfitting), nor does it provide analyses that explain root causes or prescribe targeted fixes — the authors only demonstrate which environmental styles trigger more errors and measure internal coverage, leaving causal diagnosis and mitigation for future work.",
